title: GIRLS SOCCER: Eagles shut out Braves
text:
GIRLS SOCCER: Eagles shut out Braves Times Sports Staff Finger Lakes Times | 0 comments 
ONTARIO — The Wayne Central girls soccer team got its postseason off to a strong start Wednesday, thanks in part to Adrianna VanCuyck and Hannah Mitchell. 
The duo accumulated four goals and three assists as the second-seeded Eagles shut out No. 15 Canandaigua 5-0 in a Section V Class A opener. 
VanCuyck piled up two goals and two assists, while Mitchell chipped in two scores and set up another for Wayne (16-1). Taylor Gabriel accounted for the other goal. Goalkeeper Bailey Jenkins stopped four shots. 
No. 4 Greece Arcadia 3, No. 13 Geneva 0 
GREECE — Sarah Bonsu corralled 10 shots in goal for the Panthers, who finished the season 8-8-1. 
Lily Schultz netted a pair of first-half goals to spark the Titans (13-3-1). 
CLASS D1 
No. 7 Mount Morris 2, No. 10 Honeoye 1 
MOUNT MORRIS — Sara Jane Stevens tied the game 1-1 in the 25th minute of the second half for Honeoye (5-12). 
Mount Morris’ Lauren Ferraro chalked up her second goal of the game in the 73rd minute. 
CLASS D2 
No. 4 Belfast 3, No. 13 Romulus 0 
COHOCTON — Emma Voorhees made eight saves in net for Romulus (1-15).
